@startuml obc_input_to_cpc_charge_enable_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title OBC Input To CPC Charge Enable Signal Flow\n(OBC plug/charger state -> CPC charge-enable publication)

participant "OBC\ncharger-state producer" as OBC #E8F7E8
participant "BAT_BMS\npack-state producer" as BMS #E8F0FE
participant "Vehicle state\nDriveState" as Veh #F4F7FB
participant "CPC\ncharge-port owner" as CPC #FFF4CC
participant "Charge observers" as Obs #FCE8FF

== Charge-Port Inputs ==

OBC -> CPC : frmObcStateMsg\nObcState / AcPlugState
BMS -> CPC : frmBatBmsStateMsg\nBmsState / PackSoc / PackTemp
Veh -> CPC : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\nDriveState
activate CPC
CPC -> CPC : normalize stale OBC / BMS / vehicle inputs
CPC -> CPC : derive PlugState / ChargeEnable
CPC -> CPC : derive ThermalState / ChargeTargetSoc
note right of CPC
Representative outputs
- PlugState
- ChargeEnable
- ThermalState
- ChargeTargetSoc
end note

== Charge-Port Publish ==

CPC -> Obs : frmChargePortStateMsg
CPC -> Obs : traceable charge-port enable /\nthermal publication
deactivate CPC

note over OBC, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. OBC provides charger state and AC plug visibility
2. CPC combines OBC, BAT_BMS, and vehicle state
3. CPC derives charge-enable and thermal outputs
4. Charge-port observers confirm charging readiness
end note

@enduml
